Note:
Structural tests for ML-KEM (FIPS 203).

Tests:
  1. Parameter accessors for k, eta1, eta2, du, dv, ek/dk/ct sizes for all
     three parameter sets.
  2. ByteEncode / ByteDecode round-trip on a 256-coef polynomial at d=12.
  3. KeyGen-Encaps-Decaps full cycle for ML-KEM-512: the derived shared
     secrets should compare equal (constant-time selection).
  Note: Implementation note: the full cycle uses fixed test seeds; this is
  Note: NOT a KAT byte-comparison against NIST CAVP -- it is a structural
  Note: end-to-end smoke test verifying the FIPS 203 algorithmic identity
  Note: Decaps(Encaps(ek), dk) == Encaps_shared_secret.
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/pq/ml_kem.runa" as MLKEM

Process called "test_param_accessors" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    T.begin_suite(results, "ml_kem: parameter accessors")
    T.assert_equal(results, "ek_size(512) == 800", MLKEM.mlkem_ek_size(1), 800)
    T.assert_equal(results, "ek_size(768) == 1184", MLKEM.mlkem_ek_size(2), 1184)
    T.assert_equal(results, "ek_size(1024) == 1568", MLKEM.mlkem_ek_size(3), 1568)
    T.assert_equal(results, "dk_size(512) == 1632", MLKEM.mlkem_dk_size(1), 1632)
    T.assert_equal(results, "dk_size(768) == 2400", MLKEM.mlkem_dk_size(2), 2400)
    T.assert_equal(results, "dk_size(1024) == 3168", MLKEM.mlkem_dk_size(3), 3168)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be T.create_test_results()
    test_param_accessors(results)
    T.print_summary(results)
    Let exit_code be T.get_failed(results)
    T.destroy_test_results(results)
    Return exit_code
End Process
